This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 31, 2012, as Cesar Chavez Day. It highlights the life and work of Cesar Chavez, a civil rights leader who fought for the rights of migrant farm workers in California. The proclamation recognizes Chavez's advocacy for social justice and his use of nonviolent methods to bring about change. It also mentions the commemoration of the UFW's birthplace and the naming of a US Navy ship after Chavez. The proclamation calls on all Americans to honor Chavez's legacy through service, community, and education programs.